name: UKErevyen-13: Jubalong [Live]
description: A 2 hour review, part of the student festival UKA in 2013 in Trondheim. Over 30 performances for full houses at Studentdersamfundet. Music by Christian Aftret Eriksen and Gaute Eliassen. The band, called Larschens Lævende Lydmageri, was Ingrid Gausemel Remøy (violin), Helge Huldt-Nystrøm (saxophones), Andrea Otterstad Johansen (flute, saxophones), Kristina Rystad (trumpet), Einar Kjensmo Fuglerud (guitar, banjo, mandolin), Hans Henrik Grønsleth (keys and accordion), Magnus Leite (bass) and Kristoffer Rystad (drums).

name: Best of the 80s [Live]
description: Got to play all those guilty pleasures for our fellow students at a packed 80's party at Samfundet in Trondheim back in 2013. Great fun! Mathias Molund Indergård (vocals), Hans Henrik Grønsleth (synths), Hans Christian Bollingmo (guitars), Arnstein Dahle Svanholm (guitars), Magnus Molund Indergård (bass), Martin Fjellseth (drums), Elisa Keeling (backing vocals), Mia Katrine Nilsen (backing vocals), Lina Hopaneng Ingeborgrud (backing vocals).
